+# PR-214 Remediation Report
+
+## Thread Triage
+
+- `T-214-01`: actionable
+- `T-214-02`: duplicate of `T-214-01`
+- `T-214-03`: obsolete
+- `T-214-04`: actionable
+- `T-214-05`: actionable
+
+The triage source of truth is `artifacts/review/thread_triage.json`, using exact thread ids from `.github/review_export/pr_214_threads.json`.
+
+## Changes Made
+
+- `src/policy/approval_router.py`: normalized the inbound approval state before delegating to preview payload construction so `manual_review` resolves to `human_review_required` for both live and fallback responses.
+- `src/policy/preview.py`: preserved `approval_state` and `requires_human_review` in the fallback `preview_unavailable` payload.
+- `tests/test_preview.py`: expanded fallback assertions and added a regression test for `preview_enabled=False` with `approval_state="manual_review"`.
+- `docs/approval_policy.md`: updated the fallback example to include `approval_state` and `requires_human_review`.
+
+## Intentionally Not Applied
+
+- `T-214-02`: no separate change because it duplicates the reopened fallback regression already fixed under `T-214-01`.
+- `T-214-03`: no change because the thread is outdated and proposes reviving a legacy branch on the current code path.
+
+## Verification
+
+- `python3 -m unittest tests.test_preview tests.test_approval_router`
+- Result: `Ran 5 tests ... OK`
+
+- Direct payload check:
+
+```python
+build_policy_preview(
+    request_id="req-214",
+    approval_state="manual_review",
+    preview_enabled=False,
+    actor="review-bot",
+)
+```
+
+- Observed payload:
+
+```python
+{
+    'request_id': 'req-214',
+    'status': 'preview_unavailable',
+    'actor': 'review-bot',
+    'approval_state': 'human_review_required',
+    'requires_human_review': True,
+}
+```
